I"L<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/self-alignment-guides-meaning-making">Identity</a> is the main drive behind <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/motivated-reasoning-distorts-judgement">motivated reasoning</a>. The <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-states-modulate-feelings">feeling</a> of the sublime refers to becoming <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perception-is-context-dependent">aware</a> of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cosine-similarity-is-magnitude-agnostic">magnitude</a> and grandeur of things larger than ourselves (e.g. universe, nature, life). This feeling implicitly also reduces the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/self-model-of-consciousness-mechanizes-sentience">importance of the self</a>, and in this is a tool against motivated reasoning.</p>
